1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,400
Space and time aren't separate; they’re one fabric, curved by mass-energy.

2
00:00:04,400 --> 00:00:08,000
This concept, called spacetime, is pivotal in understanding relativity.

3
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:12,400
Imagine a trampoline, where the surface bends under a heavy ball.

4
00:00:12,400 --> 00:00:14,400
That's spacetime reacting to mass.

5
00:00:14,400 --> 00:00:19,200
Researchers have shown that light bends around massive objects, confirming this interaction.

6
00:00:19,200 --> 00:00:24,000
Understanding spacetime reveals how gravity works, altering our perception of the universe.

